Program: The Reith Lectures
Title: A New Politics of the Common Good
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00lb6bt
Last Broadcast Date: Sat 4 Jul 2009
Professor Michael Sandel delivers four lectures about the prospects of a new politics of the common good. The series is presented and chaired by Sue Lawley. Sandel makes the case for a moral and civic renewal in democratic politics. Recorded at George Washington University in Washington DC, he calls for a new politics of the common good and says that we need to think of ourselves as citizens, not just consumers. Show less